@startuml
!theme plain
title Component Diagram – Layered Architecture (4+1 View)

' === Define layers using packages with consistent styling ===
package "Presentation Layer (Frontend)" {
    [Next.js Dashboard] as Frontend
    [Thunder Client] as Client
    [Swagger UI] as Swagger
}

package "Application Layer (Controllers)" {
    [ProductsController] as ProdCtrl
    [IndexingDemoController] as IndexCtrl
    [QueryOptimizationController] as QueryCtrl
    [ConcurrencyDemoController] as ConcurCtrl
    [AsyncVsSyncController] as AsyncCtrl
}

package "Business Logic Layer (Services & Strategies)" {
    [BenchmarkService (Singleton)] as Benchmark
    [IndexedQueryStrategy] as IndexedStrat
    [NonIndexedQueryStrategy] as NonIndexedStrat
    [RawSqlQueryStrategy] as RawSqlStrat
}

package "Data Access Layer (Repository & ORM)" {
    [IProductRepository (Interface)] as RepoInterface
    [ProductRepository (Implementation)] as RepoImpl
    [Entity Framework Core (DbContext)] as EF
}

database "Database Layer" {
    database "Oracle Database 21c XE" as DB
}

' === Connections between layers (top to bottom) ===

' Presentation → Application
Frontend --> ProdCtrl : HTTP API calls
Client --> ProdCtrl : HTTP GET/POST/PUT/DELETE
Swagger --> ProdCtrl : HTTP documentation & testing

' Application → Business
ProdCtrl --> Benchmark : records metrics
ProdCtrl --> RepoInterface : calls repository methods
IndexCtrl --> Benchmark : records metrics
IndexCtrl --> IndexedStrat : uses for fast query
IndexCtrl --> NonIndexedStrat : uses for slow query
IndexCtrl --> RawSqlStrat : uses for raw SQL
QueryCtrl --> (no business layer) : self-contained benchmarks
ConcurCtrl --> (no business layer) : self-contained concurrency
AsyncCtrl --> (no business layer) : self-contained async demos

' Business → Data Access
IndexedStrat --> EF : executes queries via LINQ
NonIndexedStrat --> EF : executes queries via LINQ
RawSqlStrat --> EF : executes raw SQL
RepoImpl ..|> RepoInterface : implements
RepoImpl --> EF : calls DbContext methods

' Data Access → Database
EF --> DB : SQL queries (Oracle dialect)

' === Notes explaining each layer ===
note top of Frontend : HTML/CSS/JS (Next.js static export)\nConsumes REST API\nServed via UseStaticFiles()
note left of ProdCtrl : Handles HTTP requests\nContains endpoint logic
note right of Benchmark : Singleton pattern\nCollects all performance measurements
note right of RepoInterface : Repository pattern\nAbstracts data access
note bottom of EF : Unit of Work pattern\nTracks changes, commits transactions
note bottom of DB : PRODUCTS table\nIndex on PRODUCT_NAME\nRowVersion column

' === Color coding layers (optional) ===
' Uncomment if you want colors:
' package Presentation Layer #LightBlue
' package Application Layer #LightGreen
' package Business Logic Layer #LightYellow
' package Data Access Layer #LightCoral
' database Database Layer #LightGray

@endumld